> **Internal Document** - Implementation guide for the interactive demo with Astro.js + deck.gl
>
> **Source of Truth**: `docs/RFQ.md` only
>
> **Primary Feature**: Planning View with Sandbox Mode (What-If Scenarios)

---

## 1. Visual Mood & Design Philosophy

### 1.1 Design Reference: Linear App

We adopt Linear's visual mood as our design foundation - not its solutions, but its aesthetic sensibility.

<img src="https://linear.app/static/og/default.png" alt="Linear App - Design Reference" width="800"/>

**What we take from Linear:**
- Minimalist, focused interface
- Dark mode as default
- Generous whitespace
- Subtle borders and shadows
- Smooth micro-interactions
- Typography-first hierarchy

**What we solve differently:**
- Railway maintenance planning (not software projects)
- Mileage-based scheduling (not sprint-based)
- 12-year strategic view (not quarterly roadmaps)
- What-if simulation mode (not just viewing)

